ENTRY            30322   20260327   20260508   20260508       3222
SUBENT        30322001   20260327   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                 19         65
TITLE      Cross-sections of 14 MeV neutron reactions producing
            short-lived nuclides.
AUTHOR     (J.Janczyszyn, L.Gorski)
INSTITUTE  (3POLITJ)
REFERENCE  (J,JRC,14,201,1973)
REL-REF    (M,,J.Janczyszyn+,J,CA,17,703,1972)
            Experimental detail
           (M,,J.Janczyszyn+,J,RRL,8,363,197112)
            Brief description of experiment.
FACILITY   (CCW) Neutron generator. In order to obtain the
            irradiation times 0.1 to 1 sec. A deflecting electrode
            was placed in the generator tube.
INC-SOURCE (D-T) T(d,n)He reaction.
INC-SPECT  14 MeV neutrons, flux was 5 x 10.**7 to
            2x 10.**8 n/cm2/sec.
DETECTOR   (NAICR) NaI(Tl) 3 * 3 inch, with a 400-channel analyser
            Victoreen ST 400 dm.
           (SCIN) Scintillation counter, Hornyak NE 450, with a
            photomultiplier EMI6097F for neutron monitoring.
METHOD     (ACTIV) Cyclic neutron activation method with the
            0.2 sec. fast pneumatic tube system (mean velocity
            30 m/s). Each sample was irradiated for 3 half-lives
            of the investigated nuclide. Counting time equaled
            irradiation time, unless shortening was necessary to
            avoid decay from long-lived nuclides. After a pause
            of 5-10 half-lives, a second measurement with the
            same counting time was performed.
MONITOR    (29-CU-63(N,2N)29-CU-62,,SIG)
           Neutron flux was determined on the basis of the 'Texas
            convention',R.L.Heath,Proc.Intern.Conf.Modern Trends
            in Activation Analysis,College Station,Texas,1965,
            p.389.
           *Specification of Texas convention, The effective
            fluxes for sample activations are to be measured by
            exposing high-purity copper disks of 0.25-mm thickness
            and 1 cm and/or 2.5 cm diameter for 1 min to
            the n-flux to be measured. ----And the disintegration
            rate of 62Cu activity is determined. Then the flux is
            given in disint./min/(gram of copper).
PART-DET   (DG,B+) Decay gammas or decay beta+.
CORRECTION The dead time of the multichannel analyser was
            corrected
ANALYSIS   When the same isomer arises from two different isotopes
           of the same elements as a result of the (n,n') and
            (n,2n) reactions, the weighed mean cross-section was
            calculated, taking isotopic abundances as weights.
DECAY-DATA Mainly taken from the Table of Isotopes,Lederer et al.,
           6th ed.,1967.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
COMMENT    In a few cases the conversion coefficient is not
            known, and is assumed to be 0 with the number of
            quanta per disintegration to be 1.
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by Janczyczyn with notes, 29/04/1976.
           (TABLE,,J.Janczyszyn+,J,JRC,14,201,1973) Table 1
HISTORY    (19760203C) KO.
           (19760519A) KO. -Add 'Aprvd',inf.on half-life of In-114
            and author's correction of Ce-140(n,2n) x-section.-
           (19900130A)VOF.-Iso-quant changed to Reaction formalism
                          Standard changed to monitor formalism
                          Resid-nuc deleted.
           (19930224U) HW.-Mispunch in BIB section corrected.-
           (19940705U) HW.-Reaction code altered in san 021.-
           (20090125A) BIB section updated
           (20100303A)SD:Evaluator remark was added to Sub.022.002
           (20260327A) VT. Revision in 008-011, 013-015, 017, 019
ENDBIB              65
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV
14.
ENDCOMMON            3
