SUBENT        30322012   20100531   20100809   20100806       3145
BIB                  6         27
REACTION  1(49-IN-115(N,2N)49-IN-114-L,,SIG)
          2(49-IN-115(N,2N)49-IN-114-M1,,SIG)
DECAY-DATA1(49-IN-114-L,0.042SEC)
          2(49-IN-114-M1,2.5SEC)
             leading to first metastable state of In-114 with
             half-life of '2.5 sec'.
           Note by compiler= (modified after author's note,4/1976)
             this half-life of 2.5 sec,which was erroneously cited
             in the Table 2 of Chemia Analityczna,17(1972)703 and
             in Radiochem.Radioanal.Letters,8(1971)363  as '2.3
             sec',  was taken from the following report,
                P.Dupont-Gautier, S.Chantelot, N.Moisson,
                     Rapport C.E.A.-R 2830, (1967).
             and the gamma energy detected is given as 150 keV.
            * a number of quanta per disintegration is assumed 1.0
SAMPLE     In(2)-O(3).
COMMENT    Compiler's note :
            'DATA2' could be cross-section of In-115(n,g)In-116-m3
           as half-life '2.5 sec' is not reported in the chart of
           nuclides and data quoted by authors is aprox. 10 times
           lower than data for a shorter m-state.
CRITIQUE  2Evaluator's remark: Suspicious data. Value for cross
           section and error more than 100 times lower.
HISTORY    (19900130A) VOF.-Reaction corrected+comment added
                     decay-data added . Pointers used
                     data block recoded.(same data)
           (20100303A) SD: Evaluator remark was added.
